<!-- If this is a letter or similar with an opener (with content such as dateline and/or salute) add it. For example: -->
<opener>
<lb/><add place="margintop" rend="left vertical gray small" hand="#U"><!-- diagonal -->C/4/49</add> <space extent="1" unit="words"/><add place="margintop" rend="right gray small" hand="#U1">MS 7/8</add>
<lb/><dateline><space extent="2" unit="words"/><placeName><geogName type="river"><choice><orig>Zambesi</orig><reg>Zambezi</reg></choice></geogName></placeName> <date when="1858-06-26">26<hi rend="underline">th</hi> June     
<lb/><space extent="4" unit="words"/>1858</date></dateline>
<lb/><space extent="3" unit="words"/><add place="inspace" rend="gray" hand="#U2"><unclear><del type="strikethrough"><gap extent="1" unit="chars"/></del></unclear> <date when="1858-08-27"><choice><abbr>Aug</abbr><expan>August</expan></choice> 27/<choice><abbr>58</abbr><expan>1858</expan></choice></date></add><!-- It looks like a note has been made here by another hand. I am not sure how to encode this. JM --><!-- Fixed. AW -->    
<lb/><salute>My Dear <persName>M<hi rend="sup underline">r</hi> Conyngham</persName></salute>
</opener>
<lb/><p><space extent="5" unit="chars"/>I am just going
<lb/>into the Launch Ma Robert
<lb/>to sail away up this
<lb/>river from the Pearl
<lb/>I have been up all
<lb/>night writing and now
<lb/>feel ashamed to give
    
    <pb facs="liv_001335_0002" n="0002"/>
<lb/>but one word - you will
<lb/>no doubt hear how we
<lb/>are obliged to part with
<lb/>the Pearl as it was
<lb/>too big for us and
<lb/>we were under such
<lb/>terribly stringent orders
<lb/>not to risk her remaining
<lb/>in the river &amp;c. that 
<lb/>I got quite a load off
<lb/>my mind when I could
<lb/>say off with you to

    <pb facs="liv_001335_0003" n="0003"/>
<lb/><placeName><country>Ceylon</country></placeName> though many loads
<lb/>must be carried in the
<lb/>poor little Ma Robert before
<lb/>we reach our destination.
<lb/>You must give me
<lb/>another ship a decent
<lb/>little paddle and not a
<lb/><measure>160 <choice><abbr>ft</abbr><expan>feet</expan></choice></measure> <del><gap extent="1" unit="words"/></del> that could
<lb/>not back though she
<lb/>saw a bank at her
<lb/>nose. <!--Tweet -AA -->The <term type="animal">hippopotami</term>
<lb/>can't stomach a 
<lb/>steamer at all. They   
    
    <pb facs="liv_001335_0004" n="0004"/>
<lb/>tumble head over heels
<lb/>to get out of her way
<lb/>I shall write you a longer
<lb/>tale next time.</p>
<lb/><p>This is the <date when="1858-06-26">26 June</date>
<lb/>will it do for a certificate
<lb/>of my existence on the
<lb/><date when="1858-06-30">30<hi rend="underline">th</hi></date> <space extent="2" unit="chars"/>If so tell <persName>Mr. Coutts</persName>
<lb/>to draw for my salary
<lb/>Here I am and no mistake
<lb/>witness my hand!</p>
<lb/><closer><space extent="2" unit="chars"/><signed><persName>David Livingstone</persName></signed></closer>


            </div>
